The Monaco Board of Statistics said that 80.2% of divorce cases which were dealt with in the Principality in 2008 had involved a couple with children.

Of these, over 50% of the parents lived in Monaco, while only 6.2% lived in the Alpes Maritimes, 3.1% in the Var and 16.2% abroad.

In a significant minority of cases (16%), the more frequent parent isn't the mother, with the latter institution cease to be the sole carer of the children.
